'''Lorenzo Guerini''' (born 21 November 1966) is an Italian [[politician]], member of the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]]. On 9 December 2013 he was nominated by the new Secretary [[Matteo Renzi]], spokesperson of the party and on 28 March 2014, Vice-Secretary along with [[Debora Serracchiani]].

==Biography==
Guerini joined [[Christian Democracy (Italy)|Christian Democracy]] in 1980s and then he became a member of the [[Italian People's Party (1994)|Italian People's Party]] in 1994.<ref>http://www.lettera43.it/politica/lorenzo-guerini-il-braccio-destro-di-matteo-renzi_43675120903.htm</ref>

In 1995 he was elected President of the [[Province of Lodi]] and after ten years, in 2005 he became the mayor of Lodi with 54.1% of votes.<ref>http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2005/aprile/06/Guerini_Unione_subito_eletto_Combattero_co_5_050406008.shtml</ref>

After [[2013 Italian general election|2013 general election]] Guerini was elected in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]. On 9 December 2013 he was nominated spokesman of the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] and few months later Vice-Secretary of the party.

